## 🎨 DESIGN SYSTEM — CORE RULES

### Colors — NEVER hardcode hex values
```
--color-bg:           #050505   ← page background, always
--color-panel:        #0a0a0a   ← cards, panels, nav
--color-cyan:         #00f5ff   ← primary accent
--color-green:        #39ff14   ← secondary accent
--color-text:         #c8c8c8   ← body text
--color-text-dim:     #555555   ← labels, meta
--color-border:       rgba(0,245,255,0.15)
--color-border-active:rgba(0,245,255,0.8)
--color-error:        #ff4444
--color-white:        #ffffff   ← display headings only
```

If a color is not in this list → do not use it. Ever.

### Typography — NEVER mix the two fonts in one element
```
Orbitron      → headings, section titles, project titles, buttons,
                 stat numbers, hero name, nav logo
JetBrains Mono→ everything else — body, labels, terminal, badges,
                 HUD tags, data cards, timestamps
```

### Spacing — NEVER use arbitrary pixel values
```
--space-1: 8px   --space-2: 16px  --space-3: 24px  --space-4: 32px
--space-6: 48px  --space-8: 64px  --space-12: 96px --space-16: 128px
```

### Shape — NEVER use border-radius > 0
```
border-radius: 0 on everything.
No rounded corners. No pill shapes. Hard edges only.
Exception: CustomCursor (it's a circle).
```

### Glows — NEVER use black box-shadows
```
Use only: --glow-cyan, --glow-cyan-sm, --glow-cyan-lg
          --glow-green, --glow-green-sm, --glow-green-lg
No shadows that use rgba(0,0,0,...) anywhere in the UI.
```

### Section Headings — ALWAYS follow this exact format
```
// CHAPTER [XX] — [NAME]
```
`//` prefix in --color-cyan, chapter number in --color-text-dim,
name in --color-white. Always uppercase. Always Orbitron.

