## 📱 RESPONSIVE RULES

When building any UI component, always ask:
**"What does this look like and do on mobile?"**

Mobile rules (< 768px):
- No parallax effects
- No 3D card tilt
- No custom cursor (hidden)
- No particle field (or < 20 particles)
- No chromatic aberration
- No terminal easter egg (keyboard-based)
- Stacked single-column layouts
- Reduced animation distances (y: 20 not y: 40)
- Reduced font sizes (use clamp values from design-system.md)

Always use this import for responsive checks in components:
```typescript
const isMobile = window.matchMedia('(max-width: 767px)').matches
```

